{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QfmUpb6vPz3VvA1nHpiawf","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F13 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC §6.6 — User Profiles:\n6\t\n7\t**`GET /api/users`**\n8\t\n9\t- Query params: `q` (search string), `limit`, `cursor`.\n10\t- Returns a list of users matching the search query with cursor-based pagination.\n11\t\n12\t**`GET /api/users/[id]`**\n13\t\n14\t- Returns:\n15\t```json\n16\t{\n17\t  \"resolved_id\": \"user@example.com\",\n18\t  \"first_seen\": \"...\",\n19\t  \"last_seen\": \"...\",\n20\t  \"identity_cluster\": {\n21\t    \"user_ids\": [\"user@example.com\"],\n22\t    \"device_ids\": [\"device-abc\", \"device-xyz\"]\n23\t  },\n24\t  \"events\": [...]\n25\t}\n26\t```\n27\t\n28\tFrom SPEC §4.3 — Resolved identity:\n29\t- Resolved identity is `coalesce(e.user_id, m.user_id, e.device_id)`.\n30\t- Uses `identity_mappings FINAL` JOIN at query time.\n31\t\n32\t## Dependencies\n33\t\n34\tCompleted features this builds on:\n35\t- F1 (`features/F1-done.md`) — ClickHouse client singleton (`src/lib/clickhouse.ts`)\n36\t- F2 (`features/F2-done.md`) — Migration script with `events` and `identity_mappings` tables\n37\t- F4 (`features/F4-done.md`) — Identity resolution logic (`src/lib/identity.ts`) — provides `queryEventsWithResolvedId`, `EventRow`\n38\t- F7 (`features/F7-done.md`) — Events list route with cursor pagination (pattern reference)\n39\t\n40\tFiles that will be imported or extended:\n41\t- `src/lib/clickhouse.ts` — ClickHouse client singleton\n42\t- `src/lib/identity.ts` — `EventRow` type, `queryEventsWithResolvedId` function (reused for user event timeline)\n43\t\n44\t## Files to create or modify\n45\t\n46\t- CREATE `src/lib/users.ts` — user search query, user profile query, types\n47\t- CREATE `src/app/api/users/route.ts` — `GET /api/users` handler\n48\t- CREATE `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts` — `GET /api/users/[id]` handler\n49\t- CREATE `src/lib/__tests__/users.test.ts` — unit tests for user query logic\n50\t- CREATE `src/app/api/users/__tests__/route.test.ts` — unit tests for `GET /api/users` route handler\n51\t- CREATE `src/app/api/users/[id]/__tests__/route.test.ts` — unit tests for `GET /api/users/[id]` route handler\n52\t\n53\t## Implementation order\n54\t\n55\t1. **Create `src/lib/users.ts`** — Define types (`UserListItem`, `UserProfile`, `UserSearchOptions`) and implement two query functions:\n56\t   - `searchUsers(options)` — queries distinct resolved identities from events joined with identity_mappings FINAL, filtered by `q` (ILIKE match on resolved_id), with cursor-based pagination (`cursor` = last resolved_id from previous page, lexicographic ordering). Returns `{ users: UserListItem[], next_cursor: string | null }`.\n57\t   - `getUserProfile(resolved_id)` — queries first_seen, last_seen, identity cluster (all user_ids and device_ids associated with this resolved_id), and recent events. Returns `UserProfile | null`.\n58\t\n59\t2. **Create `src/lib/__tests__/users.test.ts`** — Unit tests for `searchUsers` and `getUserProfile` with mocked ClickHouse client.\n60\t\n61\t3. **Create `src/app/api/users/route.ts`** — `GET /api/users` handler. Parses `q`, `limit` (default 50, max 200), `cursor` from query params. Calls `searchUsers`. Returns `{ users, next_cursor }`.\n62\t\n63\t4. **Create `src/app/api/users/__tests__/route.test.ts`** — Unit tests for the route handler (validation, param forwarding, error handling).\n64\t\n65\t5. **Create `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts`** — `GET /api/users/[id]` handler. Extracts `id` from route params. Calls `getUserProfile`. Returns the profile or 404 if not found.\n66\t\n67\t6. **Create `src/app/api/users/[id]/__tests__/route.test.ts`** — Unit tests for the user profile route handler.\n68\t\n69\t## Sprint contract\n70\t\n71\t- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits 0 with 0 failures\n72\t- [ ] Linter → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n73\t- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n74\t- [ ] Build → `pnpm build` exits 0\n75\t- [ ] File `src/lib/users.ts` exists and exports `searchUsers` and `getUserProfile`\n76\t- [ ] File `src/app/api/users/route.ts` exists and exports `GET`\n77\t- [ ] File `src/app/api/users/[id]/route.ts` exists and exports `GET`\n78\t- [ ] HTTP check: start dev server, `GET http://localhost:3000/api/users` → response is JSON with `users` array and `next_cursor` key\n79\t- [ ] HTTP check: start dev server, `GET http://localhost:3000/api/users?q=nonexistent_xyz_test` → response contains `\"users\":[]`\n80\t- [ ] HTTP check: start dev server, `GET http://localhost:3000/api/users/test-nonexistent-user-id-999` → response status is 404\n81\t\n82\t## Test plan\n83\t\n84\t- **Test file**: `src/lib/__tests__/users.test.ts`\n85\t- **Module under test**: `searchUsers`, `getUserProfile` from `src/lib/users.ts`\n86\t- **Cases to cover**:\n87\t  - `searchUsers`: returns users list with resolved_id, first_seen, last_seen, event_count\n88\t  - `searchUsers`: applies `q` filter (generates ILIKE condition in query)\n89\t  - `searchUsers`: respects `limit` parameter, caps at 200\n90\t  - `searchUsers`: applies cursor for pagination (generates condition in query)\n91\t  - `searchUsers`: returns `next_cursor` when result count equals limit, null otherwise\n92\t  - `searchUsers`: returns empty array when no results\n93\t  - `getUserProfile`: returns profile with resolved_id, first_seen, last_seen, identity_cluster, events\n94\t  - `getUserProfile`: identity_cluster includes all associated user_ids and device_ids\n95\t  - `getUserProfile`: returns null when resolved_id not found\n96\t\n97\t- **Test file**: `src/app/api/users/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n98\t- **Module under test**: `GET` from `src/app/api/users/route.ts`\n99\t- **Cases to cover**:\n100\t  - Returns 200 with `{ users, next_cursor }` on valid request\n101\t  - Forwards `q`, `limit`, `cursor` params to `searchUsers`\n102\t  - Returns 400 when limit is not a positive integer\n103\t  - Defaults limit to 